Degenerated Leukocyte Count

value.value: The determination of the amount of degenerated leukocytes (leukocytes that show deterioration in form or function) present in a sample.

label.value: Electrical Lead Locking Type

value.value: The type of locking device used to securely fasten the electrical leads to the device.

label.value: Electrocauterization

value.value: To destroy tissue using an electrical current. This process may be used to kill certain types of small tumors or to seal off blood vessels to stop bleeding.

label.value: Electrochemiluminescence

value.value: A method in which electromagnetic radiation, in the form of light emission, is generated from an electrochemical reaction in a solution.

label.value: Electrochemiluminescence Immunoassay

value.value: A method in which electromagnetic radiation, in the form of light emission, is generated from an electrochemical reaction in a solution due to the formation of antigen-antibody complexes.

label.value: Enzymatic Colorimetry

value.value: A type of colorimetry that makes use of an enzymatic reaction to induce a color change.

label.value: Enzyme Multiplied Immunoassay Technique

value.value: A type of homogenous immunoassay in which sample is applied to a reagent mixture of enzyme-labeled ligand, antibody, and substrate. Substrate binding to enzyme leads to inactivation and unlabeled-ligand in the sample can be quantified by colorimetric analysis.

label.value: Erythrocyte Agglutination Measurement

value.value: The determination of the amount of erythrocyte agglutination present in a sample.

label.value: Experimental Organism Basal Cell Adenoma

value.value: A benign epithelial neoplasm with a uniform, monomorphic appearance that is dominated by basal cells. (SEND)

label.value: Experimental Organism Basal Cell Carcinoma

value.value: A malignant epithelial neoplasm arising from basal cells. (SEND)

label.value: Geldanamycin

value.value: A benzoquinone antineoplastic antibiotic isolated from the bacterium Streptomyces hygroscopicus.  Geldanamycin binds to and inhibits the cytosolic chaperone functions of heat shock protein 90 (HSP90).  HSP90 maintains the stability and functional shape of many oncogenic signaling proteins; the inhibition of HSP90 promotes the proteasomal degradation of oncogenic signaling proteins that may be over-expressed or overactive in tumor cells. (NCI04)

label.value: Allovectin-7/Interleukin-2
Expiratory Reserve Volume

value.value: The maximum volume of air a subject can exhale from the lungs after a tidal exhalation.

label.value: Full Brother

value.value: A male who shares with his sibling the genetic makeup inherited from both of the biological parents.

label.value: Full Sister

value.value: A female who shares with her sibling the genetic makeup inherited from both of the biological parents.

label.value: Gas Chromatography Mass Spectrometry

value.value: An analytical technique wherein gas chromatography is coupled to mass spectrometry in order to separate, identify, and quantify substances in a sample.

label.value: Granulicatella elegans

value.value: A species of facultative anaerobic, gram-positive, cocci shaped bacteria assigned to the phylum Firmicutes. This species is non-motile, non-spore forming and catalase and oxidase negative. G. elegans is commensal, being found in normal human oral flora, but may be associated with infective endocarditis.

label.value: Hansel Staining Method

value.value: A microscopy staining method that utilizes Hansel reagent to differentiate eosinophils and neutrophils in a specimen. (NCI)

label.value: Heinz Body to Erythrocyte Ratio Measurement

value.value: The determination of the ratio of the erythrocytes that contain heinz bodies compared to total erythrocytes present in a sample. The measurement may be expressed as a ratio or percentage.

label.value: Hemoglobin A1C to Hemoglobin Ratio Measurement

value.value: The determination of the ratio of the glycosylated hemoglobin compared to total hemoglobin present in a sample. The measurement may be expressed as a ratio or percentage.

label.value: Hemolytic Index

value.value: The determination of the amount of destruction of red blood cells present in a sample.

label.value: Histone Antibody Measurement

value.value: A measurement of histone antibodies present in a sample.
